thread.title: Paul, Trump campaign in Nevada next week
thread.title_full: Paul, Trump campaign in Nevada next week | Las Vegas Review-Journal

author: Ben Botkin
title: Paul, Trump campaign in Nevada next week
text:
Republican presidential contenders Rand Paul and Donald Trump will visit Nevada next week.
The first to come here will be Paul, a U.S. senator from Kentucky. He plans to open his campaign's Nevada office at 5:30 p.m. Monday at 1110 Palms Airport Drive, Suite 120, Las Vegas.
Paul will swing from Las Vegas to Pahrump on Tuesday. He'll have a public event at 8:30 a.m. at the Bob Ruud Center, 400 N. Highway 160.
To register for the Las Vegas event, visit http://www.eventbrite.com/e/rand-paul-las-vegas-office-opening-tickets-1... .
To register for the Pahrump event, visit http://www.eventbrite.com/e/rand-paul-meet-and-greet-pahrump-nevada-tick... .
Trump will speak in Northern Nevada at noon Thursday at The Nugget Casino, 1100 Nugget Ave., Sparks. Doors for that event will open at 10:30 a.m.
To register for Trump's event, visit https://www.eventbrite.com/e/donald-j-trump-rally-in-reno-tickets-192099... .
Both candidates are running in a crowded field of more than a dozen GOP candidates.
Nevada is an early voting state, with February caucuses that play a key role in determining who gets the nomination.
